cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI. 

This paper deals with the algebraic approach to the theory of databases, specifically the natural join and inner union operations in relational lattices. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves lattice theory and the decidability of equational theory, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The use of algorithms to decide the equality of lattice theoretic terms implies cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on the theory of databases and the use of lattice theory suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
